WEBVTT

00:00:01.459 --> 00:00:04.960
What do the following have in common?

00:00:04.960 --> 00:00:13.460
Build an ark, choose 300 men, march around the city seven times,

00:00:13.460 --> 00:00:17.460
follow this route to the Red Sea.

00:00:17.460 --> 00:00:19.460
Did you figure it out?

00:00:19.460 --> 00:00:24.460
Jehovah was providing his people with direction.

00:00:24.460 --> 00:00:28.460
And in the case of these examples, sometimes that direction

00:00:28.460 --> 00:00:34.460
could appear to be, let's say, a bit unusual.

00:00:34.460 --> 00:00:38.460
It's not too hard for us to imagine Noah responding,

00:00:38.460 --> 00:00:43.460
and you want me to build a massive ark, or Gideon asking,

00:00:43.460 --> 00:00:49.460
just 300 men against an army of 135,000?

00:00:49.460 --> 00:00:52.460
Are you sure?

00:00:52.460 --> 00:00:57.460
Or Joshua replying, march around Jericho seven times,

00:00:57.460 --> 00:01:00.460
and just blow our horns?

00:01:00.460 --> 00:01:03.460
That's it?

00:01:03.460 --> 00:01:07.459
O Moses saying, why are we headed to the Red Sea

00:01:07.459 --> 00:01:10.459
when I believe there is a much more direct route

00:01:10.459 --> 00:01:13.459
to the promised land?

00:01:13.459 --> 00:01:18.459
They all could have responded in such ways.

00:01:18.459 --> 00:01:20.459
But did they?

00:01:20.459 --> 00:01:23.459
Let's allow the Bible to help us find the answer.

00:01:23.459 --> 00:01:26.459
Genesis chapter 6.

00:01:26.459 --> 00:01:30.459
In Genesis chapter 6, verse 22,

00:01:30.459 --> 00:01:37.459
we find that Noah did according to all that God had commanded him.

00:01:37.459 --> 00:01:41.459
He did just so.

00:01:41.459 --> 00:01:49.459
In fact, in the examples we've mentioned, they all did just so.

00:01:49.459 --> 00:01:53.459
The direction might not have been what they expected,

00:01:53.459 --> 00:01:57.459
but they humbly made the mental turn, so to speak,

00:01:57.459 --> 00:02:03.459
and they followed the divine guidance wherever it was taking them.

00:02:03.459 --> 00:02:08.460
And because they did, they saved not only themselves,

00:02:08.460 --> 00:02:11.460
but all those that were with them.

00:02:11.460 --> 00:02:16.460
Clearly, the one leading them was Jehovah,

00:02:16.460 --> 00:02:20.699
and by their responsive actions,

00:02:20.699 --> 00:02:24.699
they were in effect saying to him,

00:02:24.699 --> 00:02:28.699
where you go, I will go.

00:02:28.699 --> 00:02:33.699
Well, what about you dear graduates here before us today?

00:02:33.699 --> 00:02:36.699
Like those faithful ones of old,

00:02:36.699 --> 00:02:41.699
you are not alone in navigating your way.

00:02:41.699 --> 00:02:45.699
Jehovah is where he has always been.

00:02:45.699 --> 00:02:49.699
At the helm, guiding his people.

00:02:49.699 --> 00:02:53.699
The only difference is today,

00:02:53.699 --> 00:02:59.699
Jehovah is providing direction through his faithful and discreet slay.

00:02:59.699 --> 00:03:02.699
And it is due to our limited understanding

00:03:02.699 --> 00:03:09.699
that at times the direction may appear to be a bit unusual.

00:03:09.699 --> 00:03:14.699
Nonetheless, you have followed that direction,

00:03:14.699 --> 00:03:19.699
no matter what it was, no matter where it was taking you.

00:03:19.699 --> 00:03:24.699
And for that, we want to say thank you.

00:03:24.699 --> 00:03:28.699
In fact, we want to thank all of you in our listening audience

00:03:28.699 --> 00:03:33.699
for being responsive toward the direction providing.

00:03:33.699 --> 00:03:37.699
But we think especially you dear Gilead graduates

00:03:37.699 --> 00:03:40.699
before us today, now why?

00:03:40.699 --> 00:03:44.699
Because during the five months that we have spent with you,

00:03:44.699 --> 00:03:46.699
we saw you.

00:03:46.699 --> 00:03:51.699
We saw how you closely followed the direction of the faithful slave.

00:03:51.699 --> 00:03:54.699
You did just so.

00:03:54.699 --> 00:03:59.699
For example, when presenting your student assignments,

00:03:59.699 --> 00:04:01.699
you did so in English,

00:04:01.699 --> 00:04:06.699
even though for most of you, that was not your mother tongue.

00:04:06.699 --> 00:04:09.699
And when COVID protocols were set in place,

00:04:09.699 --> 00:04:12.699
we saw you follow all of them,

00:04:12.699 --> 00:04:15.699
even though they might have been inconvenient,

00:04:15.699 --> 00:04:19.699
in order to keep you and your classmates healthy.

00:04:19.699 --> 00:04:21.699
And when you were given counsel,

00:04:21.699 --> 00:04:23.699
not only from your instructors,

00:04:23.699 --> 00:04:26.699
but from each other,

00:04:26.699 --> 00:04:28.699
you expressed gratitude for it

00:04:28.699 --> 00:04:34.110
and immediately went to work out applying it.

00:04:34.110 --> 00:04:38.110
We saw you growing your love for one another,

00:04:38.110 --> 00:04:42.110
for God's organization, for Jehovah,

00:04:42.110 --> 00:04:44.110
and for His Son Jesus.

00:04:44.110 --> 00:04:50.110
All of this was a direct result of your sensitivity

00:04:50.110 --> 00:04:54.579
to the direction of the faithful slave.

00:04:54.579 --> 00:04:58.579
But what about after you leave this place?

00:04:58.579 --> 00:05:03.579
Even if you are assigned back to the country of origin,

00:05:03.579 --> 00:05:07.579
